    {
      "beat_id": "B01",
      "scene": "B01_VagueVsSpecific",
      "narration_text": "Compare two prompts: 'Write a summary' versus 'Write a 3-sentence summary of the following document in plain language suitable for a non-expert reader. Include the main finding, the method, and the limitation.' Both are requesting a summary. One specifies length, register, audience, and three required components. The second prompt eliminates dozens of valid interpretations. That is the value of specificity.",
      "voice": "am_onyx",
      "engine": "kokoro",
      "shot": {
        "manim": {
          "scene_class": "B01_VagueVsSpecific",
          "src": "scenes.py",
          "rendered": {
            "out": "manim/B01.mp4",
            "at": ""
          }
        }
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B01.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 21.35,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B01.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim:B01_VagueVsSpecific",
        "at": "2026-07-17T00:48:52"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B02",
      "scene": "B02_SpecificityDimensions",
      "narration_text": "Specificity has four dimensions. Length: how long? Format: what structure? Audience: who is reading? Required components: what must be in the output? Most vague prompts leave all four unspecified. Each unspecified dimension is a degree of freedom for Claude to fill with its default. Default may not be wrong — but it may not be what you needed. Specify every dimension you care about.",
      "voice": "am_onyx",
      "engine": "kokoro",
      "shot": {
        "manim": {
          "scene_class": "B02_SpecificityDimensions",
          "src": "scenes.py",
          "rendered": {
            "out": "manim/B02.mp4",
            "at": ""
          }
        }
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B02.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 19.22,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B02.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim:B02_SpecificityDimensions",
        "at": "2026-07-17T00:48:52"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B03",
      "scene": "B03_GoldenRule",
      "narration_text": "The golden rule: treat Claude like a capable new employee who has no context. A new employee does not know your house style, your audience assumptions, or your edge-case preferences. Tell them explicitly. The difference between a vague prompt and a specific one is the difference between 'help with this' and a proper brief. Write the brief.",
      "voice": "am_onyx",
      "engine": "kokoro",
      "shot": {
        "manim": {
          "scene_class": "B03_GoldenRule",
          "src": "scenes.py",
          "rendered": {
            "out": "manim/B03.mp4",
            "at": ""
          }
        }
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B03.mp3",
